200.Name: Elefauna Flower
200.Desc: This lucky charm has to be picked from an Elefauna right before evolution

201.Name: Woodsman's Axe Head
201.Desc: One of the famous Woodsman's Axe heads. Still sharp

202.Name: Lake Azore Pearl
202.Desc: A rare pearl from the bottom of Lake Azore

203.Name: Blessed Pollen
203.Desc: Pollen blessed with nature’s harmony, its essence fortifies the bearer with gentle resilience

204.Name: GK's Slippers
204.Desc: Legendary slippers stolen from GK's Palace, imbued with untold speed

205.Name: Pamboo Cane
205.Desc: A cane radiating the sea's healing power, its touch revives vitality as in the days of ancient healers

206.Name: Flower of Despair
206.Desc: A bloom exuding mysterious power. Its dark energy sharpens the wielder’s strength

207.Name: Elemental Explosion
207.Desc: An artifact holding the fury of elements. Its tempestuous power amplifies elemental force

208.Name: Frozen Claws
208.Desc: Shards of frost-bound power and warmth. Their presence fortifies the body against all harm

209.Name: Ship Captain's Log
209.Desc: This is a journal kept by the captain of the ship between Volcano Island and Sunfall Kingdom

210.Name: Emerald Scales
210.Desc: These gem scales were shed by the powerful Patrik, and are impressively tough

211.Name: Gold Piece Die
211.Desc: The Gold Piece Die is a magical device that is powered by pure strength

212.Name: Dark Warro Thorn
212.Desc: Thorns dropped by Dark Warro are rare and highly valued

213.Name: Monastery Idol
213.Desc: An idol found in Volcano Island, infused with vitality and resilience

214.Name: Forging Hammer
214.Desc: The constant clanging from the Forging Hammer will make any Miscrit a bit irascible

215.Name: Stony Shield
215.Desc: A shield crafted from lava rocks pulled straight from the Volcano itself

216.Name: Skyline Peak Gem
216.Desc: Chiseled from the famous golden gem atop Skyline Peak

217.Name: Shattered Gatestone
217.Desc: The Shattered Gatestone is made of some of the hardest material ever found in Miscria

218.Name: Shard of Dawn's Landing
218.Desc: The Shard of Dawn's Landing is a stream of pure light energy that has been crafted into a solid object

219.Name: Bauble of the Dawn
219.Desc: The Bauble of the Dawn fills any Miscrit that wears it with pure energy, giving them an extra boost

220.Name: Shackler’s Gem
220.Desc: A gem guarded by arcane sorcery. Its energy protects the wielder from all forces

221.Name: Mushles
221.Desc: A peculiar relic whispering otherworldly secrets, found in hidden forests

223.Name: Dark Owlie Feather
223.Desc: This feather was shed by Dark Owlie during flight, and found near the peaks of Mount Gemma

224.Name: Cloud Cake
224.Desc: The clouds surrounding the very peak of Monk's Mountain provide incredible sustenance

225.Name: Eternal Falls Mushroom
225.Desc: The enduring mushrooms that grow behind the Eternal Falls are nearly impossible to obtain

226.Name: Skelepup's Spark
226.Desc: Skelepup's Spark contains a concentrated jolt of power that revs up your Miscrit

227.Name: Obsidian Lava
227.Desc: This relic has been infused with the same lava that flows through Obsidape's paws

228.Name: Helzbelz Bells
228.Desc: The ringing of the Helzbelz Bell awakens something deep within a Miscrit

229.Name: Bean Stalk
229.Desc: This relic is made from a fragment of the Aerobian Bean Stalk

230.Name: Monk's Robe
230.Desc: The Monk's Robe hides something terribly powerful inside

231.Name: Nero's Orb
231.Desc: This orb, once played with by a young Nero, was found in a Monk's Mountain cave

232.Name: Tiki Idol
232.Desc: The Tiki Idol from the Enchanted Tiki Island has been worshipped for many generations

233.Name: Lost Swords
233.Desc: These swords survive as relics from an earlier age of Miscria

234.Name: Gravitron Pebble
234.Desc: This pebble floats with a mysterious other-worldly energy

235.Name: Arrow of Love
235.Desc: This arrow from Valentino's quiver contains the ultimate power of love

238.Name: Frost Root
238.Desc: A rare root from the frozen wastelands, warding off the embrace of slumber

239.Name: Quartex Crystal
239.Desc: Crystal with a chilling energy that freezes the mind, protecting against confusion

240.Name: Temple Stone
240.Desc: This stone, obtained from the crumbling Temple walls, contains deep magic

241.Name: Vanquished Soul
241.Desc: This relic was found in the Volcano, and is believed to be the spiritual remnants of an ancient Miscrit

242.Name: Magicite Staff
242.Desc: The mysterious floating stones on top of the Magicite Staff contain great and terrible power

243.Name: Molten Coin
243.Desc: This molten coin from deep within the Fountain of Doom is dangerously powerful

244.Name: Frozen Coin
244.Desc: This coin was found on an expedition to the mysterious Ice Tower

245.Name: Cage of Despair
245.Desc: This cage is symbolic of the hardships of Miscrits throughout the world

246.Name: Saiyam's Trident
246.Desc: This magical trident contains a spell to increase strength

247.Name: Shard of Rudolffe
247.Desc: This ancient shard is imbued with magic and the power to enhance

248.Name: Gog's Cog
248.Desc: This rugged part from complex innards of Gog gives him incredible physical strength

249.Name: Flying Carpet Fragment
249.Desc: Torn from the corner of an Aerobian carpet and made into a powerful relic

250.Name: Charcoal Idol
250.Desc: No one is sure if the Charcoal Idol was an object of worship or simply a child's doll that has been badly charred

251.Name: Moon Rock
251.Desc: This rock, pulled from the surface of the Moon of Miscria, is nearly indestructible

252.Name: Scent of Skustunk
252.Desc: The Scent of Skustunk is at once mystifying, horrifying, and intriguing

253.Name: Echino Shell
253.Desc: This shell hardened from battle, has a varied effect on Miscrits

254.Name: Fractured Shell
254.Desc: The Fractured Shell is shed by Fracture as it matures, but it maintains an aura of magic

255.Name: Dark Wind's Venom
255.Desc: Dark Wind's Venom is extracted from its killer fangs, then morphed into a powerful relic

256.Name: Leggy Eggs
256.Desc: The eggs from Leggy found in Sunfall Shores have an incredibly hard shell

257.Name: Petrified Mama Baby
257.Desc: This Petrified Mama baby relic was uncovered during a Volcano dig

258.Name: Petrified Dragon Egg
258.Desc: No one knows how to reawaken this egg, though many have tried to harness its magic

259.Name: Volcano Banner
259.Desc: The harsh environment of the Volcano requires one to be of strong stock

260.Name: Forest Banner
260.Desc: This banner is given to the new Forest Guard upon completion of their training

261.Name: Jungle Banner
261.Desc: This banner is carried by the fearless Guard of the Miscrian Jungle

262.Name: Monk's Mountain Banner
262.Desc: The frigid cold of Monk's Mountain requires good health and good physical condition

263.Name: Sunfall Shores Banner
263.Desc: This banner is carried by the Guard of Sunfall Shores

264.Name: Mt. Gemma Banner
264.Desc: The rocky terrain of Mt. Gemma requires one to be an excellent climber and fleet of foot

265.Name: Everlasting Snowball
265.Desc: This snowball manages to remain chilly to the touch even in bright sunlight

266.Name: Peepsie Eggs
266.Desc: Peepsie Eggs are extremely colorful and sweet

267.Name: Truncherous Hammer
267.Desc: This brutally powerful relic is difficult for most Miscrits to carry

268.Name: Papa's Antlers
268.Desc: The protective strength of Papa lies deep within these sacred antlers

269.Name: Nanaslug's Horn
269.Desc: This slimy, sludgy horn of Nanaslug increases both Health and Elemental Attack

270.Name: Geotoad Teeth
270.Desc: This relic is crafted from the chips of Geotoad Teeth that are mined in Mount Gemma

271.Name: Patchkin's Rind
271.Desc: The source of the haunting Patchkin's power

272.Name: Dragon Shackle
272.Desc: Temporary placeholder for Aerobian Compass rework

273.Name: Mystic Map
273.Desc: This Mystic Map was a gift from a traveler, and no one knows where it leads

274.Name: Palmda's Talon
274.Desc: Palmda's Talon is impossibly sharp, and makes any physical attack more powerful

275.Name: Nox's Nightmare
275.Desc: Temporary placeholder for Cactolin's Thorn rework

276.Name: Cactus Flower
276.Desc: A flower from one of the hardy, spiny cacti of Mount Gemma
